New and Changed Objects in Retail Execution

Do more with the new and updated Retail Execution objects.

Use these tour and route custom objects to support Direct Store Delivery and Van Sales feature:

* cgcloud__Route_Template__c object for setting up route types for various markets
* cgcloud__Route__c object for creating routes that act as a blueprint for creating tours
* cgcloud__Route_Account__c object for adding customers to a route
* cgcloud__Tour__c object for creating executable trips
* cgcloud__Tour_Check__c object for creating or editing the vehicle and security checks of a tour
* cgcloud__Tour_Object_Reference__c object for defining allowed visits, signatures, and document types of a tour
* cgcloud__Tour_Template__c object for defining tour settings for various markets
* cgcloud__Vehicle__c object for storing vehicle details
* cgcloud__Vehicle_Warehouse__c object for storing the relationship between a vehicle and a warehouse

New fields:

* cgcloud__Should_Allow_End_Day_Geofencing__c, cgcloud__Should_Allow_End_Day_GPS_Tracking__c, and cgcloud__Should_Allow_End_Day_Time_Tracking__c for enabling GPS tracking and time tracking at the end of the day
* cgcloud__Should_Allow_Start_Day_Geofencing__c, cgcloud__Should_Allow_Start_Day_GPS_Tracking__c, and cgcloud__Should_Allow_Start_Day_Time_Tracking__c for enabling GPS tracking and time tracking at the start of the day
* cgcloud__Creation_Platform__c for determining the platform that a user can create a tour on
* cgcloud__Default_Tour_Visit_Duration__c for setting the default duration of a visit in a tour
* cgcloud__Is_Odometer_Photo_Required__c for requiring the documentation of odometer reading at the start and end of the day with a picture
* cgcloud__Geofence_Distance__c for setting the maximum distance allowed between the driver's GPS location and the warehouse or customerâ€™s location during the start, end, or visit of a tour
title: New Features in Retail Execution
